{d:1,q:"Premature infants are at highest risk for respiratory distress syndrome because:",opts:["Their airways are too small","Surfactant production is insufficient before 34-36 weeks gestation causing alveolar collapse","All of the above","None of the above"],ans:1,exp:"Surfactant reduces alveolar surface tension and prevents collapse. Premature infants lack sufficient surfactant causing alveolar collapse and respiratory failure requiring positive pressure ventilation."},
